    "scenarioId": "scenario_1",
    "title": "The Alderman's Ruin",
    "daysAllowed": 30,
    "startingText": "A foreign factor has entered the town quietly, carrying letters of introduction that may — or may not — be genuine.\n\nLord Edric Fenn holds the aldermanship with an iron hand. In twelve days the autumn tax assessment begins. If Fenn is still in office, your patron's candidate loses another term.\n\nYou have thirty days. You have your wits. And you have a story that no one has heard yet.",
    "victoryText": "The petition arrived at dawn — seven signatures, including Prior Aldous himself.\n\nLord Edric Fenn stepped down from the alderman's chair before midday. He did not look well.\n\nYou were already three days' ride away when word reached the capital.",
    "failTexts": {
      "exposed": "The Guard Captain's eyes found you across the Market Square.\n\n\"I've been watching you,\" he said. \"The Tavern, the Chapel steps, the widow's door. You've been very busy for a traveler with no business here.\"\n\nHe didn't arrest you. He didn't need to. By evening, the whole town knew your face.",
      "timeout": "The autumn tax rolls were signed. Lord Edric Fenn's seal was already dry.\n\nSomewhere the story you planted still traveled — changed, embellished, half-forgotten. But the window had closed. Your patron's patience had not."
    },
